{% comment %} Weather Circles — half_vertical (400x480), 2-day view.
  Built on framework classes (flex/layout/gap/grid/typography) per TRMNL's
  review feedback; custom CSS is only for what the framework has no utility
  for, or where the behaviour needs to be certain inside a real mashup tile
  (this repo has been bitten by mashup-vs-standalone sizing differences
  before — see git history on full.liquid/.layout): alignment (avoiding
  limited_inline_styles), flex-grow/min-height (plain flex:1, not the
  framework's stretch-x/y, since those resolve differently depending on
  the direct parent's classes and we'd rather not gamble on that inside a
  mashup), inline SVG icon sizing, the absolute temp overlay, the
  day-divider border, and sizing a day block by its actual cell-row count
  (data-rows). lg: variants bump icon size for TRMNL X. .wc-body carries its
  own inner padding: the framework's own --gap already separates the tile
  from the screen edge, but our own content had nothing reserved between it
  and *that* boundary, so text ran flush against it. title_bar stays outside
  .wc-body so its background remains full-bleed. .wc-curtxt gets a negative
  margin to pull it in from the circle's icon box: the box reserves room for
  the wind barb in every direction, so the drawn circle only fills ~49% of
  its own width -- most of the visual gap to the temperature text is empty
  SVG margin, not the flex gap. The same empty barb margin is why the grid
  cells overlay their temp absolutely in the plot box's top-left corner
  (diagonally NW of the drawn circle, not stacked N above the whole box) and
  pull the time label up under the circle with a negative margin: both sit
  in space the SVG reserves but rarely uses. When the barb itself heads into
  the NW corner (wind from ~WNW..NNW) the payload sets c.tpos to wc-tp-ne
  and the temp flips to the NE corner instead (see temp_side in
  trmnl_report.py). A barb pointing S can still reach the time label --
  accepted, the barb halo keeps it legible. {% endcomment %}
<style>
  .wc-body   { flex:1; min-height:0; padding:6px 10px; }
  .wc-cur    { align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:4px 0;
               border-bottom:2px solid #000; }
  .wc-cur svg{ width:100px; height:100px; }
  .wc-curtxt { align-items:flex-start; margin-left:-8px; }
  .wc-days   { flex:1; min-height:0; }
  .wc-day    { flex:1; min-height:0; }
  .wc-day[data-rows="2"] { flex-grow:2; }
  .wc-day + .wc-day { border-top:2px solid #000; }
  .wc-dayhdr { align-items:baseline; }
  .wc-row    { flex:1; align-items:center; }
  .wc-cell   { align-items:center; gap:0; }
  .wc-plot   { line-height:0; position:relative; }
  .wc-plot svg{ width:58px; height:58px; }
  .wc-plot .value { position:absolute; top:1px; left:0; line-height:1; }
  .wc-plot .value.wc-tp-ne { left:auto; right:0; }
  .wc-cell .label { margin-top:-9px; }
  .grow      { flex:1; }
  .trmnl .screen--lg .wc-cur svg { width:130px; height:130px; }
  .trmnl .screen--lg .wc-plot svg { width:74px; height:74px; }
</style>

<div class="wc flex layout--col h--full">
  <div class="wc-body flex layout--col">
    <div class="wc-cur flex layout--row gap--small">
      {{ current.svg }}
      <div class="wc-curtxt flex layout--col">
        <span class="value value--large lg:value--xlarge">{{ current.temp }}&deg;</span>
        <span class="title title--small lg:title--base">{{ current.summary }}</span>
        <span class="value value--xsmall">H {{ current.high }}&deg; &middot; L {{ current.low }}&deg;</span>
        <span class="label label--small">{{ current.wind }}</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wc-days flex layout--col">
      {% for d in days %}
      <div class="wc-day flex layout--col" data-rows="{{ d.rows }}">
        <div class="wc-dayhdr flex layout--row gap--small">
          <span class="title title--small lg:title--base grow">{{ d.label }}</span>
          <span class="label label--small">H {{ d.high }}&deg; &middot; L {{ d.low }}&deg;</span>
        </div>
        <div class="wc-row grid grid--cols-4 lg:portrait:grid--cols-2">
          {% for c in d.cells %}
          <div class="wc-cell flex layout--col">
            <div class="wc-plot">
              <span class="value value--xxsmall {{ c.tpos }}">{{ c.temp }}&deg;</span>
              {{ c.svg }}
            </div>
            <span class="label label--small">{{ c.label }}</span>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="title_bar">
    <span class="title">Weather Circles</span>
    <span class="instance">{{ location }} &middot; {{ generated_at }}</span>
  </div>
</div>
